A: C B D
B: A C E G
C: A B D
D: C A
E: G F B
F: G E
G: F B
It will be in the following order
A C B E G F D
A->C Since C is listed first the first visit will be C
C->B since A is considered already visited the DFS will visit the next listed node
B->E in similar manner to previous one
E->G
G->F
G<-F returning to previous node since both G and E are marked as visited(not a visit just backtracking)
E<-G returning to previous node
B<-E returning to previous node
C<-B
C->D since D is not marked as visited
C<-D both c and a are marked as visited
A<-C returning to original node
it ends there since both B and D were marked as visited before.